'''''lheben''''' is a [[Noldorin]] word meaning "five".<ref name=LR>{{LR|Etymologies}}, p. 368</ref><ref name=AI>{{HM|AI}}, pp. 92, 150 (note 6)</ref><ref>[[Rhona Beare]], "Conjectures on the Origin of Quenya", in {{PE|6}}</ref>

==Etymology==

*[[Sundocarme|Root]] [[LEP#Other versions|LEP]]<ref name=LR/>

==Examples==

*Phrase on a draft of [[Thrór's Map]]: "'''''Lheben''' [[tâl|teil]] [[brand (word)#Noldorin|brann]] [[i]] [[annon]] [[ar]] [[nêl|neledh]] neledhi [[gar]] [[godrebh]]''" ("'''Five''' feet high the gate and three by three they go through together"<ref name=AI/> or "'''Five''' feet high the door and three may walk abreast"<ref>{{H|1}} (translation by [[Gandalf]] of the [[Old English]] [[runes]] on the map)</ref><ref>[http://www.jrrvf.com/~glaemscrafu/texts/cartedethror-a.htm Thrór's map inscription] at [http://www.jrrvf.com/haut.shtml Jrrvf.com] (accessed 27 June 2011)</ref>)
